Description¶

Developer module containing custom data structures.

class msTools.core.py.structures.EqualitySet(iterable=None)¶

Bases: object

Abstract baseclass for compiling an ordered set of non-equivalent data, designed specifically for non-hashable types.

Provides a templated interface to each subclass based on the abstract DATA_TYPE property. This property must be overridden in order to specify the type of accepted input data.

Designed to mimic a set whilst internally data is compiled through equality testing instead of a hash table. Expect operations to run in O(n) time compared to their set counterparts which are likely to run in O(1) time.

DATA_TYPE¶

Template property which defines the accepted data type for the interface.

Note

Abstract property - must be overriden by each subclass.
